    "body": "@MadelineMurray thanks for your response. Essencialy, I have a [Besu test ledger running](https://hub.docker.com/r/hyperledger/cactus-besu-all-in-one/dockerfile), I'm [creating a simple contract](https://gist.github.com/RafaelAPB/3828bf5fb48f9d89e73b415a725b8f2e), issuing transactions, and then trying to fetch the contract storage, via this.web3.eth.getStorageAt. That's when I always obtain 0x0 for all variables and constants. I believe this is because of the private transaction feature of Besu. Furthermore, I believe that \"the private equivalent of https://web3js.readthedocs.io/en/v1.2.0/web3-eth-contract.html hasn't been implemented yet\", which may correspond to this issue. Any thoughts on that? ",
